{
  "doc_id": "40490",
  "text": "In this study, some indexes of insulin resistance, such as IR HOMA or simple plasma fasting insulin, were associated with the waist circumference of the girls. This finding is not surprising because all but five of the girls had a waist circumference above the 90th centile of the reference for age and sex. Previous studies in prepubertal children have shown that subjects with a waist circumference above the cut-off value of the 90th centile for age and sex have a high risk of obesity-related morbidity [CITATION_1] ). In addition, in our sample, more than 20% of girls had three or more metabolic or cardiovascular risk factors.",
